editorialNotes.standard: Everyone needs a task manager—and Things is adaptable enough for anyone. This Apple Design Award winner is crisp and lightweight, featuring a simple but effective interface. The ever-present Magic Plus button makes it easy to add to-dos from anywhere in the app, and organizing items is as simple as dragging them where you want them. It’s like the unicorn of productivity tools: deep enough for serious work, surprisingly easy to use, and gorgeous enough to enjoy staring at.

editorialNotes.standard: Working out regularly is great, but good health truly begins in the kitchen. This visually dazzling app offers dozens of meal ideas in clever categories like low-carb lunches and post-exercise snacks. Brilliant photos and simple instructions make these recipes easy to follow even for novice chefs, and the built-in shopping list groups items together by grocery-store aisle for shopping efficiency. Now all we need is an app that forces us to hit the gym.
editorialNotes.short: Skip the takeout and eat healthy at home.
